The paper proposes a meta-heuristic algorithm for optimization problems, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization. The algorithm is based on the particle swarm optimization (PSO) paradigm, which is a popular technique in the field of neural networks and evolutionary computation. The paper provides a formal analysis of the algorithm's performance on two reference problems, namely sorting and OneMax, which are classic problems in the field of combinatorial optimization. This suggests that the paper could be classified under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
